TV presenter Willis Raburu has gone back to the gym, aiming to get the desired results in six months. Addressing the issue about his weight, Raburu admitted he is not okay with his weight. "I finally get to talk about this thing that has been heavy on my mind! I admit I need help with my weight," he said. Speaking on YouTube, Raburu said he started his weight loss journey on January 4 and will end it 0n June 4. "I feel like I need to do it for me, not for people. I have a six-month target. It's going to be an interesting six months. We are going to be praying against calories." The TV presenter is currently at 150kg. He said he added 4kg during the December holiday and aims to lose it by the end of January.